{"word":"ἐπισταδόν","slug":"ἐπισταδόν","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n40959\" key=\"e)pistado/n\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ἐπιστᾰδόν</orth>, <pos opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"pos\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Adv.\">Adv.</a></pos>, (<etym lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"etym\">ἐφίστημι, ἐπιστῆναι</etym>) <sense id=\"n40959.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">standing over each in turn</tr_> (<cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ἐφιστάμενος ἑκάστῳ</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg4099.tlg001:364:35\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ EM\">EM</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">364.35</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>), i.e. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">one after another, successively</tr_>, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">νείκεον ἄλλοθεν ἄλλον ἐ</foreign>. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:12:392\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">12.392</biblScope> </bibl>; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">νώμησεν δ᾽ ἄρα πᾶσιν ἐ</foreign>. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:13:54\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">13.54</biblScope> </bibl>; <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">standing by</tr_>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0001.tlg001.perseus-grc1:1:293\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ A.R.\">A.R.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.293</biblScope> </bibl>; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἐ. οὐτάζοντες</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">standing up to</tr_> each other, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0001.tlg001.perseus-grc1:2:84\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Id.\">Id.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2.84</biblScope></bibl>.—The words of <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:16:453\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">16.453</biblScope></bibl>, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">δόρπον ἐ. ὡπλίζοντο</foreign>, seem to have given rise to the other expl. of the Sch., <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἐπισταμένως, ἐμπείρως</foreign> (as if from <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἐπίσταμαι</foreign>).</sense> </entryFree>"}]}